cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.LG 

The paper deals with modelling pedestrian dynamics and routing in an evacuation scenario, which falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper deals with modelling the behaviour of a group of individuals in a network-based structure. The second likely category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the paper deals with modelling an evacuation process, which is a critical aspect of building design and safety. The third likely category is cs.RO (Robotics) as the paper deals with modelling the behaviour of agents in a dynamic environment. The fourth likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper deals with modelling the behaviour of humans in a computer-based simulation. The fifth likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper uses a cost-benefit analysis function to dynamically route pedestrians in the network.
